modules.description: Provides gradient-based optimization algorithms including Adam, Rmsprop, and Lbfgs, with support for single and double precision computations. Operates on user-defined records of parameters generated via a ppx deriver, simplifying parameter management during model training. Enables rapid development of machine learning models by abstracting low-level optimization details.

Generates OCaml structure items from type declarations using a provided path and location. Operates on OCaml AST nodes and type declarations to inject custom code. Used to automate the creation of optimized or specialized implementations for numerical computing libraries.
